node.text:
The real pandemic!!! Cigarette smoking is responsible for more than 480,000 deaths per year in the United States, including more than 41,000 deaths resulting from secondhand smoke exposure. This is about one in five deaths annually, or 1,300 deaths every day. On average, smokers die 10 years earlier than nonsmokers. https://www.cdc.gov/tobacco/data_statistics/fact_sheets/fast_facts/index.htm

#4biddenknowledge #billycarson #billycarsonofficial #FACTS

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Billy Carson on September 09, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'JOIN ME LIVE FROM EGYPT W/ @BILLYCARSONOFFICIAL @4BIDDENKNOWLEDGE The Mysteries ef Egypt THUR 9/9 FRI 9/10 6pm PST 6pm PST YouTube.com/the4biddenknowledge'.

node.text: Repost @reginameredith_official I’ll be talking with @billycarsonofficial of @4biddenknowledge live TOMORROW and Friday from Cairo, Egypt to debrief some of his amazing finds on the ancient mysteries of Egypt. You can join in from any of his channels, including his YouTube channel @the4biddenknowledge. Friday we’ll be streaming live right here from my IG channel as well. Have any questions you’d like me to ask? Comment below! 👇 Hope to see you then!  #4biddenknowledge #billycarsonofficial #billycarson #saqqara

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Billy Carson on September 08, 2021 tagging @billycarsonofficial, @elisabethihoekstra, @mohamed1gamall, and @j_shah_travel. May be an image of 4 people, people standing and outdoors.

node.text:
Spent the day in #Saqqara Egypt with @elisabethihoekstra @mohamed1gamall and @j_shah_travel  Egyptologist Mohamed Gamall and Shah. We are sitting on a top of a 60-80 ton crystal granite sarcophagus lid that is sitting on top of a 60 ton crystal granite base. Inside of an impossible passageway underground. I believe we were in the Halls Of Amenti. These days called the serapium. 4biddenknowledge.com 

#4biddenknowledge #billycarson #billycarsonofficial

node.text:
I saw a 3,000-Year-Old Wooden Toe Prosthetic that was discovered on Egyptian Mummy. That's because the toe is a 3,000-year-old wooden prosthesis, which was found attached to a female mummy in an ancient Egyptian grave site. Researchers think the toe is one of the world's oldest prosthetic devices. And now, further examination of the prosthesis has divulged even more information about the one-of-a-kind artifact and the time from which it came. Technologies like modern microscopy, X-rays and computer imaging enabled a team of researchers to determine the materials and method used to make the prosthetic. For instance, their new research, which is still unpublished, found that the wooden toe was refitted several times. Based on the meticulous construction of the ancient prosthesis, the researchers determined the wearer — a priest's daughter — wanted the toe to look natural and be comfortable to wear.  

#4biddenknowledge #billycarson #billycarsonofficial
#Egypt #prosthetic
